{
  "@context": {
    "dcterms": "http://purl.org/dc/terms/",
    "gist": "https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ns/ontology/gist/",
    "gistd": "https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ns/data/gist/",
    "owl": "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#",
    "rdf": "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#",
    "rdfs": "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#",
    "skos": "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#",
    "xsd": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
  },
  "@id": "gist:idText",
  "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
  "rdfs:comment": [
    "NOTE: A common use case would be for preexisting internal company identifiers.",
    "NOTE: Often, there will be just one identifying text string. More would be appropriate if the individual had different identifiers, such as employee number and social security number. A good way to model that would be to have functional subproperties of idText, such as departmentNumber.",
    "EXAMPLE: The id text for a car is '4Y1SL65848Z411439'; the id text for the HR department of some company is H31415.",
    "DEFINITION: A text string that identifies an individual.",
    "NOTE: This property is an alternative to using the property gist:isIdentifiedBy in conjunction with instances of the class gist:ID."
  ],
  "rdfs:isDefinedBy": {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ontology/gistCore14.1.0"
  },
  "rdfs:label": "id text",
  "rdfs:range": {
    "@id": "xsd:string"
  },
  "skos:definition": "A text string that identifies an individual.",
  "skos:example": "The id text for a car is '4Y1SL65848Z411439'; the id text for the HR department of some company is H31415.",
  "skos:prefLabel": "id text",
  "skos:scopeNote": [
    "Often, there will be just one identifying text string. More would be appropriate if the individual had different identifiers, such as employee number and social security number. A good way to model that would be to have functional subproperties of idText, such as departmentNumber.",
    "A common use case would be for preexisting internal company identifiers.",
    "This property is an alternative to using the property gist:isIdentifiedBy in conjunction with instances of the class gist:ID."
  ]
}